    <div class="divider-rule"><span>Writing philosophy</span></div>

    <h2 id="philosophy">How he writes</h2>
    <p>Akshay edits with a heavier hand than he drafts. Every article on theStacc that goes through him gets read three times: once for argument, once for line-level voice, once for the small operational facts that age fastest. He thinks most B2B SaaS content fails not because the writers are bad, but because no one is checking whether the article actually helps the person reading it. Plain language. Real numbers. A clear takeaway you can act on. If a paragraph doesn't pass those three checks, it doesn't ship.</p>

    <blockquote class="author-pull">
      "Content marketing isn't a volume game anymore. It's a quality game played at volume. The teams that win are the ones who edit harder than they draft."
      <cite>— Akshay VR, Marketing Head, theStacc</cite>
    </blockquote>

